<div id="review_184085311" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/184085311" />
    <a title="Victoria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3991641-victoria"><img alt="Victoria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1301883330p2/3991641.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/184085311?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Victoria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Victoria" href="/user/show/3991641-victoria">Victoria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780671742553" href="/book/show/534564.Almost_Heaven">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=dnf">dnf</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=annoying-heroine">annoying-heroine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=annoying-hero">annoying-hero</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=waste-of-time">waste-of-time</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=horrible-heroine">horrible-heroine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=heroine-has-a-dead-wish">heroine-has-a-dead-wish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=misunderstandings">misunderstandings</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3991641-victoria?shelf=heroine-i-didnt-like">heroine-i-didnt-like</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer184085311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3875282774169732149">Going back to other books I&apos;ve read from this author I feel like I&apos;m still holding grudges against Clayton, Jason, and Jordan. Their actions against their partners were horrible. I found them way too ruthless, but their stories were compelling enough to enthrall me to the very end. Almost Heaven is a long book, 475 pages long, and I stopped reading it at page 370. The writing, as always with McNaught, was brilliant. And even though I found Elizabeth&apos;s character (unlike other McNaught&apos;s more inte</span>
  <span id="freeText3875282774169732149" style="display:none">Going back to other books I've read from this author I feel like I'm still holding grudges against Clayton, Jason, and Jordan. Their actions against their partners were horrible. I found them way too ruthless, but their stories were compelling enough to enthrall me to the very end. Almost Heaven is a long book, 475 pages long, and I stopped reading it at page 370. The writing, as always with McNaught, was brilliant. And even though I found Elizabeth's character (unlike other McNaught's more interesting heroines) shallow and predictable, the story was interesting enough to keep me engaged. Sadly, the main character's immensely stupid action made me dislike her so terribly, and my annoyance with her idiocy was such, that I lost interest in a book in which I'd had invested so much of my time. Bah!!!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3875282774169732149" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review184085311">
