        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1316855508" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3232265818933466714">I was very emotional while reading this. Despite the characters were going on their daily life okeydoke, there I was sobbing into my pillow.<br/><br/>All I wanted throughout the 500+ pages of the book was that the heroine to stop being hurt by people around her. I was rooting for her to get her happy ending ASAP. <br/><br/>But nope. We need to torture her more. The amount of misunderstanding/lack of communication in this book was extremely annoying sometimes. If only people talk!<br/><br/>But still, I fucking love this book.</span>
  <span id="freeText3232265818933466714" style="display:none">I was very emotional while reading this. Despite the characters were going on their daily life okeydoke, there I was sobbing into my pillow.<br /><br />All I wanted throughout the 500+ pages of the book was that the heroine to stop being hurt by people around her. I was rooting for her to get her happy ending ASAP. <br /><br />But nope. We need to torture her more. The amount of misunderstanding/lack of communication in this book was extremely annoying sometimes. If only people talk!<br /><br />But still, I fucking love this book. I love and adore Elizabeth. I love how much she found humour in between her downfalls. I admire her courage, her patience, understanding and all in all she was one of the perfect heroine in a HR novels for me. I also know that the hero is somewhat unlikable in some of his decision, but I also love him for his flaws, his stubbornness and his ego. He was so unlikable that he reminded me of myself. And that's a bad thing. Which made it the best thing. I don't know how to explain this. It's just that I love their relationship and story, no matter how painful and challengingly it was.<br /><br />There. If you haven't read it, do read it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3232265818933466714" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

